Six new cases of Coronavirus infection was recorded in Osun State on Friday, bringing Nigeria’s total number of confirmed Covid-19 to 190. According the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC), in its latest update Osun State is now third on the table of states with highest number of infected patients. Global record of Coronavirus has crosses one million, while over 50,000 persons have died as a result of the pandemic. The tweet update reads, “Six new cases of #COVID19 have been reported in Osun State, Nigeria. As at 11:00 am 3rd April there are 190 confirmed cases of #COVID19 reported in Nigeria. Twenty have been discharged with two deaths.”